The National Union of Mineworkers, or NUM, has signed a “substantive” one-year wage agreement with Petra Diamonds’ Cullinan diamond mine. The signed wage agreement is structured as follows: The parties also agreed that there will be an additional salary adjustment for the periods July, August and September 2018. In a press statement, the NUM noted that it is pleased that this wage negotiation was amicably concluded without hiccups. “it only took two hours to reach an agreement.” The NUM has expressed its gratitude to its members at Petra Diamonds' Cullinan mine for the manner in which they behaved during the negotiation period.mm“Our members are excited and they gave us this mandate to sign the agreement,” says William Mabapa, NUM deputy general secretary.